The article discusses the potential benefits of the Republican tax reform for the middle class. It suggests that once the reforms are implemented, middle- and lower-income earners will see their paychecks increase as tax withholding declines and their federal tax liability decreases. The article also highlights the potential for improved hiring and wages as a result of an improved corporate tax structure that helps small businesses invest and makes American businesses more competitive globally. The details of the tax plan are still being negotiated, but every version includes lower rates for middle-class earners and a larger standard deduction for lower-income Americans. The plans also aim to lower tax rates for small businesses and allow them to deduct certain expenses immediately. Overall, the article argues that the Republican tax reform will be beneficial for the middle class.